				<p>Tito Kayak poses for a portrait in front of a black Puerto Rican flag painted on a building in the neighborhood where Kayak grew up in Ponce. The black and white rendition of the Puerto Rican flag is a symbol of mourning and resistance of US rule on the island for many Puerto Ricans. Six months after Hurricane Maria, 11 percent of homes and businesses on the island are still without power.  Kayak donates his own time and expertise to fixing downed power lines and restoring electricity to those who have not yet been reached by FEMA. <br><small>Photo: Rob Gourley</small></p>
